column1: #Text=I do n't really think of myself as a born-again , and they of course insist on later baptism .
#Text=I 'm sort of currently leaning towards the Baptist church .
#Text=I do n't know ; I have n't decided --
#Text=I went through a Southern Baptist phase when I lived in Georgia .
#Text=The Southern Baptist convention is probably the most conservative out there .
#Text=If you were forced to choose , which war would you prefer to fight in , Iraq or Afghanistan ?
#Text=Which one would I rather fight in ?
#Text=On the side of the United States .
#Text=Well , at least we had an endgame .
#Text=My reasoning is completely ridiculous : I distrust men who are that skinny .
#Text=You and I are both lean , but if I told you , you 've got to go take this stump out to the backyard , and I gave you an axe , I 'd be pretty confident you could do it .
#Text=Obama does n't look like he could do it to me . [ both laugh ]
#Text=If you remain that lean on the campaign trail , when they 're having all those --
#Text=There 's something about it I distrust , a guy who ca n't lift a hammer .
#Text=Most men stop being afraid of dying .
#Text=Then , when they have kids , suddenly they 're afraid of it again .
#Text=But not for themselves , for their kids .
#Text=So I do n't really care , just as long as my kids are provided for .
#Text=You think that most men , pre-parenthood , lose their sense of mortality and their fear of it ?
#Text=I think you just get tired of being afraid of it .
#Text=Yeah , I was afraid of it in my early twenties ; and as a kid , I just remember being really , really afraid of dying , and it being incomprehensible and depressing .
#Text=We had a lizard die , and that was a big deal .
#Text=She was asking these questions , " Is it gon na be another lizard ? "
#Text=You know , she has all of these --
#Text=Yeah , she has a lot of really valid questions .
#Text=I do n't know ; I also do n't feel that we understand everything .
#Text=For all the people who praise Shakespeare , Shakespeare is still really quite extraordinary .
#Text=The sense that I have of Shakespeare is he does understand that on some level , we as human beings , our bodies , are like the top of an iceberg that you can see .
#Text=Then there 's all this other stuff under the water that you ca n't see .
#Text=I 'm not that afraid of it anymore because I feel like there 's all this other stuff under the water .
